<Text>
<![CDATA[EQU(Wrk_MSGStep,350)COP(Ref_Connection.MSG_Dest[8],Wrk_TempString.LEN,1)[GRT(Wrk_TempString.LEN,0) COP(Ref_Connection.MSG_Dest[12],Wrk_TempString.DATA[0],Wrk_TempString.LEN) CONCAT(Wrk_Instances[Wrk_RdWrIndex].Main_Read_Buffer,Wrk_TempString,Wrk_Instances[Wrk_RdWrIndex].Main_Read_Buffer) RES(Wrk_Instances[Wrk_RdWrIndex].Info.InactivityTimer) ,MOV(400,Wrk_MSGStep) ];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="35" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[Check incoming data]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[NOP();]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="36" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[This will check main read buffer for new modbus string.
First check the header (10 bytes). Bytes 4 an 5 will contain additional packet length.
If all bytes of this message are received, the packet will be extracted from the Main read buffer and parsed.
Revised in AOI Ver 2.04
]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[EQU(Wrk_MSGStep,400)MOV(410,Wrk_MSGStep)GEQ(Wrk_Instances[Wrk_RdWrIndex].Main_Read_Buffer.LEN,10)[COP(Wrk_Instances[Wrk_RdWrIndex].Main_Read_Buffer.DATA[4],Wrk_AdditionalLen,1) SWPB(Wrk_AdditionalLen,REVERSE,Wrk_AdditionalLen1) ADD(Wrk_AdditionalLen1,6,Wrk_AdditionaLenRead) ,GEQ(Wrk_AdditionaLenRead,10) GEQ(Wrk_Instances[Wrk_RdWrIndex].Main_Read_Buffer.LEN,Wrk_AdditionaLenRead) [MID(Wrk_Instances[Wrk_RdWrIndex].Main_Read_Buffer,Wrk_AdditionaLenRead,1,Wrk_ModbusPacket) ,DELETE(Wrk_Instances[Wrk_RdWrIndex].Main_Read_Buffer,Wrk_AdditionaLenRead,1,Wrk_Instances[Wrk_RdWrIndex].Main_Read_Buffer) ,OTE(Wrk_DataReceived) ] ];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="37" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[Check for malformed packets by checking transaction type and protocol identifier.   Clear the buffer  if found.  
This is just a safety measure in case corrupt data ever gets left in the buffer.
]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[EQU(Wrk_MSGStep,410)MOV(420,Wrk_MSGStep)XIO(Wrk_DataReceived)MOV(490,Wrk_MSGStep)[NEQ(Wrk_Instances[Wrk_RdWrIndex].Main_Read_Buffer.DATA[2],0) ,NEQ(Wrk_Instances[Wrk_RdWrIndex].Main_Read_Buffer.DATA[3],0) ,MOV(Wrk_Instances[Wrk_RdWrIndex].Main_Read_Buffer.DATA[8],Wrk_CmdFromReadPacketTmp) LES(Wrk_CmdFromReadPacketTmp,1) ,GRT(Wrk_CmdFromReadPacketTmp,6) NEQ(Wrk_CmdFromReadPacketTmp,15) NEQ(Wrk_CmdFromReadPacketTmp,16) ]CLR(Wrk_Instances[Wrk_RdWrIndex].Main_Read_Buffer.LEN);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="38" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[Once data is ready, clear data fields from the old packet data
Revised in AOI v2.04]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[EQU(Wrk_MSGStep,420)MOV(425,Wrk_MSGStep)[SUB(Wrk_AdditionalLen1,1,Wrk_ModbusBytes) FLL(0,Wrk_ModbusID,1) FLL(0,Wrk_ModbusUnit,1) FLL(0,Wrk_ModbusCmdString,1) ,CLR(Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket) CLR(Wrk_ModbusCmdStart) CLR(Wrk_ModbusCmdLen) ];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="39" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[Once data is ready,  extract the Modbus_ID, Modbus_Unit, and extract the data packet from the Modbus TCP packet
Revised in AOI v2.04]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[EQU(Wrk_MSGStep,425)MOV(430,Wrk_MSGStep)EQU(Wrk_ModbusPacket.LEN,Wrk_AdditionaLenRead)[MID(Wrk_ModbusPacket,4,1,Wrk_ModbusID) MID(Wrk_ModbusPacket,1,7,Wrk_ModbusUnit) MID(Wrk_ModbusPacket,Wrk_ModbusBytes,8,Wrk_ModbusCmdString) MOV(Wrk_ModbusCmdString.DATA[0],Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket) ,COP(Wrk_ModbusCmdString.DATA[1],Wrk_TempInt,1) SWPB(Wrk_TempInt,REVERSE,Wrk_ModbusCmdStart) COP(Wrk_ModbusCmdString.DATA[3],Wrk_TempInt,1) SWPB(Wrk_TempInt,REVERSE,Wrk_ModbusCmdLen) ];]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="40" Type="N">
<Text>
<![CDATA[EQU(Wrk_MSGStep,430)MOV(440,Wrk_MSGStep)[EQU(Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket,1) ,EQU(Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket,2) ,EQU(Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket,5) ,EQU(Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket,15) ]raC_Tec_NetModbusTCPServer_RespStrBit(Wrk_RSB,Wrk_ModbusCmdStart,Wrk_ModbusCmdLen,Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket,Ref_ModbusData,Wrk_ModbusCmdString,Wrk_ModbusRespString)OTL(Wrk_Instances[Wrk_RdWrIndex].WriteTrigger)MOV(480,Wrk_MSGStep);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="41" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[Analyze incoming command for REGISTER commands
Transaction Type 4.
Adresses 3xxxxx and 4xxxxx handling
Finally calling AOI _CheckWriteReply to match the Transaction ID ot the request and mark the transaction as received and AOI _RespStrWORD to unpack the data and write it to the local arrays.
]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[EQU(Wrk_MSGStep,440)MOV(450,Wrk_MSGStep)[EQU(Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket,3) ,EQU(Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket,4) ,EQU(Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket,6) ,EQU(Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket,16) ]raC_Tec_NetModbusTCPServer_RespStrWord(Wrk_RSW,Wrk_ModbusCmdStart,Wrk_ModbusCmdLen,Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket,Ref_ModbusData,Wrk_ModbusCmdString,Wrk_ModbusRespString)OTL(Wrk_Instances[Wrk_RdWrIndex].WriteTrigger)MOV(480,Wrk_MSGStep);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
<Rung Number="42" Type="N">
<Comment>
<![CDATA[Check for Exception Replies from the remote device.  This is indicated by the 8th bit being sent in the return transaction type.  i.e. Transaction type of 3 would be returned as 131 decimal.
]]>
</Comment>
<Text>
<![CDATA[EQU(Wrk_MSGStep,450)[MOV(0,Wrk_ModbusRespString.DATA[0]) MOV(3,Wrk_ModbusRespString.DATA[1]) ,OR(Wrk_CmdFromReadPacket,16#80,Wrk_ModbusRespString.DATA[2]) MOV(1,Wrk_ModbusRespString.DATA[3]) ,MOV(4,Wrk_ModbusRespString.LEN) OTL(Wrk_Instances[Wrk_RdWrIndex].WriteTrigger) ]MOV(480,Wrk_MSGStep);]]>
</Text>
</Rung>
